      problemBody: "<p>The biggest obstacle for CBD is its association with cannabis. Many still assume CBD gives a high, that it's illegal, or that it's a hippie trend without scientific basis. None of this is true.</p><p>CBD, or cannabidiol, is one of over a hundred cannabinoids in the hemp plant. It's non-psychoactive – it produces no high whatsoever. It's legal throughout Sweden and the entire EU. And the research behind it is growing explosively, with thousands of studies examining its interaction with the body's endocannabinoid system.</p><p>Another misunderstanding is that all CBD is the same. There are enormous quality differences between isolated CBD, broad-spectrum CBD, and full-spectrum CBD. The cheap CBD oil online often has nothing in common with a carefully formulated full-spectrum extract in a professional skincare product. Source, extraction method, and concentration all play decisive roles.</p>",
